{"lemma":"نُذُرُ","slug":"نُذُرُ","root":"ن.ذ.ر","root_slug":"ن-ذ-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ن-ذ-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"نَذِير","root":"نذر","pos":"N","occurrence_count":58},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["name","noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":4},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n39618","n39619","n39620"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%86%D9%8F%D8%B0%D9%8F%D8%B1%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"bringer of bad news, herald, legate, apostle, warner","examples":[{"text":"يَا أَيُّهَا النَّبِيُّ إِنَّا أَرْسَلْنَاكَ شَاهِدًا وَمُبَشِّرًا وَنَذِيرًا","english":"O Prophet, indeed We have sent you as a witness and a bringer of good tidings and a warner."},{"text":"هٰذَا نَذِيرٌ مِنَ ٱلنُّذُرِ ٱلْأُولَى","english":"This is a warner of the warners of old."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"messenger of God","tags":["broadly"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"warning","examples":[{"text":"نَذِيرُ شُؤْمٍ","english":"an ill omen"},{"text":"حِكْمَةٌ بَالِغَةٌ فَمَا تُغْنِ ٱلنُّذُرُ","english":"Extensive wisdom – but warning does not avail [them]."}]},{"pos":"name","gloss":"a male given name, Nadir"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/na.ðiːr/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n39618","headword_ar":"نَذْرٌ","root":"n*r","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A vow, which a man makes to be binding,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"obligatory, on himself;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, M, * K, * TA;) [either"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"absolutely,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"conditionally:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"na*ara","text_ar":"نَذَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":":)] pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nu*uwrN","text_ar":"نُذُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, M, K: *) and in the following verse of Ibn-Ahmar, some say that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nu*ur","text_ar":"نُذُر"},{"kind":"text","text":"is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"na*orN","text_ar":"نَذْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruhunN","text_ar":"رُهُنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rahonN","text_ar":"رَهْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; but others say that it is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"na*iyrN","text_ar":"نَذِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the sense of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mano*uwrN","text_ar":"مَنْذُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":"},{"kind":"quote","text":"kamo duwna layolaY mino tanuwfiy~apK\n                      \n                     \n                        lam~aAEapK tuno*aru fiyhaA Aln~u*uro"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"How many a waterless desert glistening with the mirage, in which vows,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"things vowed, are vowed, lie in the way to Leylà!"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S.) ―         -b2-  Also, (tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mulct for an intentional wound;"},{"kind":"text","text":"used in this sense by Esh-Sháfi'ee, (T, TA,) and of the dial. of El-Hijáz; (TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aro$N","text_ar":"اَرْشٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, A, K, TA,) which is of the dial. of the people of El-'Irák: (T, TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nu*uwrN","text_ar":"نُذُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (T, A, K:) said by Aboo-Nahshal to be"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"only for wounds, small and great."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, K. *) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"liY qibala fulaAnK na*orN","text_ar":"لِى قِبَلَ فُلَانٍ نَذْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, TS, L,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Einoda fulaAnK","text_ar":"عِنْدَ فُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A mulct for a wound is owed to me."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, K, &c.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEoTayotuhu na*ora juroHihi","text_ar":"اَعْطَيْتُهُ نَذْرَ جُرْحِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I gave him the mulct for his wound."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) Aboo-Sa'eed Ed-Dareer says that it is thus called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"liA^an~ahu nu*ira fiyhi","text_ar":"لِاَنَّهُ نُذِرَ فِيهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e., because it is made binding, or obligatory, for it; [namely, for the wound;] from the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"na*arotu ElaY nafosiY","text_ar":"نَذَرْتُ علَى نَفْسِى"},{"kind":"text","text":". (T, TA.) ―         -b3-  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A votive offering"},{"kind":"text","text":"].       -A2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nu*orN","text_ar":"نُذْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["T","TA","A","K","TS","L"]},{"entry_id":"n39619","headword_ar":"نُذْرٌ","root":"n*r","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(M) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nu*urN","text_ar":"نُذُرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, K) [and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"na*orN","text_ar":"نَذْرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(see 4)] and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"na*iyrN","text_ar":"نَذِيرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"na*iyrapN","text_ar":"نَذِيرَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ni*aArapN","text_ar":"نِذَارَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Esh-Sháfi'ee, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nu*oraY","text_ar":"نُذْرَى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K) are substs. in the sense of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ino*aArN","text_ar":"اـِنْذَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An informing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"advising, of a thing:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a warning,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cautioning, and putting one on his guard, against a thing, and putting one in fear of a thing;"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.: (see 4:)] (T, S, M, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a putting one in fear in announcing a thing."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eu*orFA","text_ar":"عُذْرًا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^awo nu*orFA","text_ar":"اَوْ نُذْرًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eu*urFA A^awo nu*urFA","text_ar":"عُذُرًا اَوْ نُذُرًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", accord. to different readings, in the Kur, lxxvii. 6, put in the accus. case as causal complements, signify"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"liloA_iEo*aAri","text_ar":"لِلْاـِعْذَارِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waA@loA_ino*aAri","text_ar":"وَا@لْاـِنْذَارِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"For excusing and warning"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Zj, T.) [See also art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"E*r","text_ar":"عذر"},{"kind":"text","text":".] And in like manner, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nu*uri","text_ar":"نُذُرِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the Kur, liv. 16, &c., signifies"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ino*aAriY","text_ar":"اـِنْذَارِى"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, K.) And so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"na*iyri","text_ar":"نَذِيرِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the Kur, lxvii. 17. (T, M.) Hence also the saying of the Arabs,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eu*oraAka laA","text_ar":"عُذْرَاكَ لَا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nu*oraAka","text_ar":"نُذْرَاكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEo*iru walaA tuno*iro","text_ar":"اَعْذِرُ وَلَا تُنْذِرْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Do thou that for which thou wilt be excused,"},{"kind":"text","text":"by inflicting punishment when it is deserved,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and do not"},{"kind":"text","text":"merely"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"warn and put in fear"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["M","T","S","K"]},{"entry_id":"n39620","headword_ar":"نُذُرٌ","root":"n*r","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nu*orN","text_ar":"نُذْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]}]}}